<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST : LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
JUDGE ASKED TO LET RAIDERS DEAL PROCEED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The city of Irwindale on Friday asked Los Angeles Superior Court Judge Charles 
E. Jones to lift his order blocking completion of final financial and 
contractual arrangements to build the proposed Raiders football stadium in the 
San Gabriel Valley community. 
</P>
<P>
A filing by Irwindale attorneys contended that in preparing and approving an 
environmental impact report on the stadium project, the city has fully complied 
with the terms of a September, 1987, court order. 
</P>
<P>
John Belcher, an attorney for Los Angeles City Councilman Ernani Bernardi, who 
brought the suit that resulted in the court issuing its temporary restraining 
order requiring a satisfactory environmental impact report, said Friday that 
his side has 10 days to contest the Irwindale filing but may decide not to do 
so. 
</P>
<P>
Should the court lift its order, Irwindale authorities will then try to secure 
financing and reach a satisfactory final deal with Los Angeles Raiders owner Al 
Davis for construction of the planned 62,500-seat stadium. 
</P>
</TEXT>
