<P>
METRO DIGEST : LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
RESTAURANT OWNER SLAIN, WIFE WOUNDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A restaurateur was killed and his wife seriously injured in a shooting early 
Friday morning at the couple's Torrance home, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Investigators said they have no suspect and few clues in the shooting of 
William and Rosemary Deardorff, owners of Vince's Spaghetti Restaurant on 
Hawthorne Boulevard in Torrance. 
</P>
<P>
The couple had returned Thursday from a vacation in Acapulco and were 
apparently asleep in their Elm Avenue home when an intruder entered their 
bedroom and shot them several times, Torrance Police Sgt. Ron Traber said. 
</P>
<P>
Rosemary Deardorff, 44, was able to call paramedics at 2:43 a.m. despite 
several gunshot wounds, Traber said. Her husband, 49, died at Torrance Memorial 
Hospital Medical Center a short time later. His wife was in fair condition and 
was scheduled to undergo surgery Friday afternoon at county Harbor-UCLA Medical 
Center. 
</P>
<P>
Robbery apparently was not a motive in the attack, police said, noting that 
money and other valuables were found inside the home. 
</P>
</TEXT>
