<P>
3 SEEN NEAR SITE OF INFANT DEATH SOUGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police were looking Friday for three people seen speeding away from near where 
a newborn boy was found strangled in a trash bin behind a Gardena motel. 
</P>
<P>
The infant was found dead Thursday morning, stuffed into a box and dumped in 
the trash bin behind the Travelodge motel, Sgt. David Morgan said. A man 
picking through the trash for aluminum cans found the body of the unidentified 
child, believed to be Asian or Latino, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said they saw three people speeding away from the area in a brown 
1977 Chevrolet Nova. 
