<HEADLINE>
<P>
IRISH USE HIGH TECH TO TRACK GUARD DOGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DUBLIN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ireland began electronically tagging guard dogs Friday after a vicious attack 
on two Dublin schoolboys by a pack of marauding German shepherds. 
</P>
<P>
Veterinary surgeons implanted electronic microchips under the skin of guard 
dogs to keep track of them, and officials set up a national register for an 
estimated 2,000 of the animals. 
</P>
<P>
The 9-year-old schoolboys were attacked outside their school last year by a 
pack of dogs and severely mauled. 
</P>
</TEXT>
