<P>
29 INDICTED ON DRUG CHARGES IN CHICAGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHICAGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Twenty-nine suspected members of a Colombian cocaine cartel have been indicted 
on federal drug charges, accused of using three Chicago-area jewelry stores as 
distributors, U.S. Atty. Anton Valukas said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
A 101-count indictment named one U.S. citizen and 28 Colombians from Cali. 
Twenty-four of those indicted were arrested Thursday night and the others were 
being sought, Valukas said. 
</P>
<P>
The local arm of the Cali cartel allegedly distributed 440 pounds of the drug a 
month, much of it through the jewelry stores. 
