<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONTROVERSY OVER TAPED POLICE 'STING' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I was saddened but not surprised to read of Jackson's racially motivated 
physical and verbal attack at the hands of the Long Beach Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
Five years ago I was pulled over, in a very similar manner, in the city of Long 
Beach. When I objected to my arm being painfully twisted behind my back during 
a body search, I was handcuffed and punched. I endured anti-Hispanic racial 
epithets from the two white officers on the way to the station and when my 
blood alcohol level was found to be less than half the legal limit, a bogus 
traffic citation was issued for another offense. 
</P>
<P>
I found that to file a complaint, you must file it with the LBPD which 
consistently finds no wrongdoing by its officers. 
</P>
<P>
DAN DUARTE 
</P>
<P>
Torrance 
</P>
