<HEADLINE>
<P>
WRITER FAILS TO SEE ALL DIMENSIONS OF SUPER BOWL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I thought that I saw an exciting, hard-fought Super Bowl this year between two 
evenly matched teams. After reading Bob Oates' analysis, I guess I stand 
corrected. 
</P>
<P>
First off, Oates states that Cincinnati peaked at midseason and that it 
remained in this game only by virtue of San Francisco "misplays" (which 
amounted to zero turnovers). 
</P>
<P>
Then he pondered the question, "Will Super Bowl XXIII be remembered for the 
49ers' mediocre performance in the first three quarters?" 
</P>
<P>
I managed to pick up a pair of three-dimensional glasses to watch the halftime 
show. 
</P>
<P>
I'd like to know where Oates was able to find a pair of one-dimensional glasses 
to watch the rest of the game. 
</P>
