<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEEKEND TV; 
</P>
<P>
46TH ANNUAL GOLDEN GLOBES TO AIR TONIGHT; CBS OBSERVES 10 YEARS OF 'SUNDAY 
MORNING' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE WEINSTEIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The show-business awards season kicks off this weekend as the Hollywood Foreign 
Press Assn. hands outs its 46th annual Golden Globes tonight at the Beverly 
Hilton. Joan Collins and George Hamilton will co-host the broadcast, beginning 
at 8:05 p.m. on cable superstation TBS. 
</P>
<P>
CBS' "Sunday Morning" celebrates its 10th anniversary with highlights from 
previous broadcasts beginning at 7:30 a.m. on Channels 2 and 8. The program 
will also include a report on endangered species and a visit to a flute 
convention in San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
"Preparing for Power: The Transition of President Bush" features an inside look 
at the man and his staff in the days preceding his ascension to the top job in 
government. Pulitzer Prize-winning journalist Hedrick Smith reports this 
one-hour documentary, airing Sunday at 10 p.m. on Channel 28. The program 
includes interviews with President and Mrs. Bush, White House Chief of Staff 
John Sununu and former Atty. Gen. Ed Meese. STEVE WEINSTEIN 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA012889-0063 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 11153 </DOCID>
