<HEADLINE>
<P>
SUSPECT EXTRADITED IN TASK FORCE CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Coos Bay, Ore., man was extradited to San Diego on Friday in connection with 
the attempted murder of a Chula Vista woman, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
An investigation by the San Diego Metropolitan Homicide Task Force led to the 
arrest Wednesday of Glesty Donald Waters, 35, a mechanic. Waters lived for 
several years in National City before moving two years ago to Coos Bay. 
</P>
<P>
Sheriff's deputies said Waters allegedly assaulted Helen Ruth Toy on Jan. 6, 
strangling her to the point of unconsciousness. Toy was released from the 
hospital the day of the incident. 
</P>
<P>
Waters' bail has been set at $300,000. He was expected to be booked into County 
Jail Friday. Sgt. Liz Foster said Waters is being held on suspicion of 
attempted murder, assault with a deadly weapon, robbery and kidnaping. 
</P>
