</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The University of Oklahoma's interim president said that the university is 
concerned about the school's football program. 
</P>
<P>
"It has become apparent there are very significant problems in the football 
program . . . " said David Swank. 
</P>
<P>
In December, the NCAA put the program on probation for 3 years, prohibiting the 
team from bowl games for 2 years and live television appearances for a year. 
</P>
<P>
Two weeks ago, starting cornerback Jerry Parks was suspended from the team and 
the school after a shooting in an athletic dormitory. Parks is accused of 
shooting with intent to injure teammate Zarak Peters. 
</P>
<P>
The university also announced that officials from the school and the Cleveland 
County district attorney's office are investigating allegations of a possible 
sexual assault last weekend at an athletic dormitory. 
