<HEADLINE>
<P>
THEY FULLY ENJOYED SEINFELD SHOW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In response to Lawrence Christon's review of Jerry Seinfeld's performance 
("Laughing on Empty," Calendar, Jan. 17), we feel he was very unfair to this 
talented comedian, not just in the review of the show but also in the attack on 
Seinfeld's person -- "the New York face, thin as a chisel." (We are not from 
New York.) 
</P>
<P>
The next time Mr. Seinfeld appears in Orange County, perhaps this critic could 
take a sense of humor instead of pen and relax and enjoy the show. 
</P>
<P>
Mr. &amp; Mrs. RUSSELL G. GORDON 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
