<HEADLINE>
<P>
ICN BIOMEDICALS CANNOT ACCOUNT FOR 14.4% DROP IN STOCK PRICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY ANN GALANTE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ICN Biomedicals Inc., a Costa Mesa medical technology firm, said it knew of no 
reason why the price of its stock fell 14.4% in active trading Friday. 
</P>
<P>
ICN Biomedicals closed at $11.125 a share Friday, down $1.875, on volume of 
53,600 shares. It was the biggest percentage loser on the American Stock 
Exchange. 
</P>
<P>
The stock has been declining steadily for several weeks. Friday's closing price 
marks a 23.9% decline from the stock's high of $14.625 per share on Jan. 12. 
</P>
<P>
ICN Biomedicals, which makes products for biotechnological research and medical 
diagnoses, has not yet reported sales and earnings for the fiscal year ended 
Nov. 30, 1988. The firm said it expects to report its annual results soon. 
</P>
<P>
For the 9 months ended Aug. 31, 1988, the company reported net income of $3.5 
million on sales of $37.6 million. MARY ANN GALANTE 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
ICN BIOMEDICALS INC 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
